ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: Lipids are fatty acid esters, an oily organic compound insoluble in water but soluble in organic solvents.

Concepts.definition: A class of hydrocarbon-containing organic compounds. Lipids are insoluble in water but soluble in nonpolar solvents and play important roles in living organisms: these roles include functioning as energy storage molecules, serving as structural components of cell membranes, and constituting important signaling molecules. Lipids can be subdivided into 2 groups: fatty acids and glycerides.
